beer.beer_description: Bocks are a strong lager style originally from the German city of Einbeck. This dark (dunkles) version showcases the rich malty flavours of German Munich malt. Smooth and medium to full bodied with some hop bitterness to balance out the malt sweetness.

items.badge_description: A traditional German lager, bock literally translates to “goat” in English. Dark and malty, bocks are so delicious one might say this beer style is the…GOAT. On Bock Beer Day go drink a bock and prove us wrong!

Thanks for staying at home, and checking in with Untappd! It allows us to stay connected to a community of beer lovers, just like you, even if we can't be in the same physical location. From our home to yours, cheers and stay safe!
